We may extend the uncertainty analysis to define a 
\emph on
correlation
\emph default
 between the uncertainties of two variables, say 
\begin_inset Formula $X(\vec{a})$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $Y(\vec{a}).$
\end_inset

 We consider the projection of the tolerance hypersphere onto a circle of
 radius 1 in the plane of the gradients 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{\nabla}X$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{\nabla}Y$
\end_inset

 in the parton parameter space 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Pumplin:2001ct,Nadolsky:2001yg"

\end_inset

.
 The circle maps onto an ellipse in the 
\begin_inset Formula $XY$
\end_inset

 plane.
 This 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

tolerance ellipse
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 is described by Lissajous-style parametric equations,
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray}
X & = & X_{0}+\Delta X\cos\theta,\label{ellipse1}\\
Y & = & Y_{0}+\Delta Y\cos(\theta+\varphi),\label{ellipse2}
\end{eqnarray}

\end_inset

where the parameter 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta$
\end_inset

 varies between 0 and 
\begin_inset Formula $2\pi$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $X_{0}\equiv X(\vec{a}_{0}),$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $Y_{0}\equiv Y(\vec{a}_{0})$
\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta X$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta Y$
\end_inset

 are the maximal variations 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta X\equiv X-X_{0}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta Y\equiv Y-Y_{0}$
\end_inset

 evaluated according to Eq.
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

(
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "masterDX"

\end_inset

), and 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi$
\end_inset

 is the angle between 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{\nabla}X$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{\nabla}Y$
\end_inset

 in the 
\begin_inset Formula $\{a_{i}\}$
\end_inset

 space, with
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\cos\varphi=\frac{\vec{\nabla}X\cdot\vec{\nabla}Y}{\Delta X\Delta Y}=\frac{1}{4\Delta X\,\Delta Y}\sum_{i=1}^{N}\left(X_{i}^{(+)}-X_{i}^{(-)}\right)\left(Y_{i}^{(+)}-Y_{i}^{(-)}\right).\label{cosphi}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


