\begin_layout Standard
The quantity 
\begin_inset Formula $\cos\varphi$
\end_inset

 characterizes whether the PDF degrees of freedom of 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $Y$
\end_inset

 are correlated (
\begin_inset Formula $\cos\varphi\approx1$
\end_inset

), anti-correlated (
\begin_inset Formula $\cos\varphi\approx-1$
\end_inset

), or uncorrelated (
\begin_inset Formula $\cos\varphi\approx0$
\end_inset

).
 If units for 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $Y$
\end_inset

 are rescaled so that 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta X=\Delta Y$
\end_inset

 (e.g., 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta X=\Delta Y=1$
\end_inset

), the semimajor axis of the tolerance ellipse is directed at an angle 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi/4$
\end_inset

 (or 
\begin_inset Formula $3\pi/4)$
\end_inset

